headline: Stock Market Today: Dow Ekes Out A Gain; Chip Equipment Names Weigh On Tech
summary: The Dow Jones Industrial Average closed with a modest gain Friday, outperforming other major indexes. In the stock market today, Palantir Technologies made a downward move, while health insurer UnitedHealth led the Dow on news that the stock is a new buy for Warren Buffett.

headline: Lululemon (LULU) Stock Trades Up, Here Is Why
summary: Shares of athletic apparel retailer Lululemon (NASDAQ:LULU) jumped 3.1% in the morning session after the firm of renowned investor Michael Burry, known for his successful bet against the housing market before the 2008 financial crisis, disclosed a new stake in the company. According to a regulatory filing, Burry's firm purchased 50,000 shares valued at nearly $11.9 million, making Lululemon 2.05% of its portfolio.
